<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Armed police have been called to Canterbury this afternoon, September 30 2020 following a report of concerns for a woman in a property.</p>

<p>The officers are in Monastery Street, with a police helicopter hovering overhead.</p>

<p>Ivy Lane and Longport have been sealed off and officers have weapons trained towards a building which backs onto Monastery Street, according to witnesses at the scene.</p>

<p>Armed police called to Canterbury, following a report of concerns for a woman in a property</p>

<p>Officers have weapons trained towards a building which backs onto Monastery Street</p>

<p>Students at the nearby Canterbury College were reportedly advised to stay on the campus as a precautionary measure while the nature of the incident was established.</p>

<p>Witnesses said at least 12 officers were on scene and that a man was seen being led from the house before being put in handcuffs, according to Kent Live. </p>

<p>This is a breaking news story. We will bring you more information as it becomes available. </p>
